Erudite Templar of Prexus<BR>Cohort Chalybeius<BR>Cazic Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Docdoertee DVine</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Quest for Group-Bulwark would be nice</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lomilar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Something similar to a LOH would be nice, a 2000 hp heal with a casting time of 2 seconds, costing 400 mana with a recast time of 5 minutes or something like that.<P>AKA: Oh'Crap Heal!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Izzel McFizzle</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">How about this one?<P>Bring Out Your Dead<P>Lvl 60 Cleric Spell<BR>Radius:  Entire Zone<BR>Effect:  96% Experience Restoration<BR>Mana: 3000 <BR>Cast time: 60 secs<BR>Recast: 1 hour<P>Description:  This spell would resurrect all corpses in the zone.<P><BR>Don't know if this spell is even possible given limitations of the EQ engine but I think it would be cool.<P>Izz<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alliliel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Btw, the Mage Epic quest *is* a spell.<P>They cast it to "Conjure" the staff that you see them holding.<P>------------------<BR><B>Alliliel Archfalcon</B><BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR><A HREF="http://www.kriegeronline.com" TARGET=_blank>Krieger</A><BR>58 Levels of Loyal Service to Tunare</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Khalim - Innoruuk</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">  Actually, along the same lines is the idea of no-drop "uber" spells from high level mobs.  It could easily be done, and would benefit the game as a whole, as well as give something back to the casting population, as opposed to making a_warrior06 better at melee.  There are multiple items in the game that give a "definite" improvement for melee classes, haste items are a good example, they increase the melee output of a melee class by a fixed percentage rate.  A warrior with an FBSS is 22% better than a warrior without as far as damage output, its written in stone and undisputable.  Better ratio weapons have the same effect, but there's nothing in the game for non-melee classes, and by putting in no-drop spells that did this, it would balance the playing fields a bit.  I'm not talking *new* spells even, I'd be happy with improvements of *old* spells, even non-combat ones would be fine, Aegolism II that costs 10% less mana to cast, someone else mentioned group BOF, thats a fine idea as well, and by making them no drop, and come from high end encounters, it helps everyone, without hurting the game, unless they really think complete heal that costs 360 mana to cast vs 400 is unbalancing.  There's spells across the board they could do this with for every class, not just the clerics.  Its easily implemented because spells can already be in the loot table, just flag them as MAGIC/NO-DROP, and its all good, and add 1 entry per spell in spdat, they already have a dozen "dummy" entries in there anyhow.<P>Just my .02<BR>Khalim Richelieu<P>P.S. I'm not going to take credit for this idea in its entirety, a lot of friends and guildmates had come up with this concept, and it would give the high end game something more for the casters out there.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Astur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The perfect level 60 quest spell: Group Aegolism. <BR><P>------------------<BR>Astur il'Ayan, Cleric of Brell<BR>Dealers of Death on Solusek Ro<BR>Profile  <A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=50334" TARGET=_blank>http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=50334</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aladain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Astur:<BR><B>The perfect level 60 quest spell: Group Aegolism. </B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I think I know why group Aego and group Bulwark will never happen.<P>Our AC buffs overwrite other classes (most) useful spells.<P>Cast an AC buff on a shaman and see what he does.<P>Heroism, however, stacks with everything.  I think this is why Verant is staying away from group-AC buffs (which is weak imo)<P>Aladain<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gello</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">On the idea of no-drop 'uber' spells...if you're willing to lose the no-drop flag, this idea was already implemented:<P>Reckoning - more uber than Retribution<BR>Reviviscence (well, store bought :P) - more uber than Resurrect<BR>Hero, BoF, Aegis, Marzin - much more uber than pre-50 buffs<BR>Aegolism - you get the picture<P>Casters get quantifiable, definite improvements to them from dropped spells.  Unfortunately there's a very strong feeling in the caster community that everything in spdat flagged for their class' use is an entitlement.  There's a profound resentment when a caster levels and doesn't have all spells of that level scribed.  (Tho casters that research may be more patient.)<P>Tho, now that I think of it, forcing spells to be no drop would dull this feeling of entitlement a lot.  (Once the caster riots subside :P)<P>Aegolism improves a cleric's buffing ability arguably as much as an fbss improves a melees offensive ability.  They both drop.  There's not a lot of difference.<P>And btw, what happens when you cast an AC buff on a shaman?  If mana is tight they're one of the first to always get an AC buff from me, due to aggro slow causes.  Not once has a shaman ever complained, but maybe they're just being nice.  What stacking issues are there?<p>[This message has been edited by Gello (edited 06-06-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Avenea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">yeah i was wondering that as well. didn't know there were any.<P>------------------<BR>-Avenea Arach'Daemos 60 High Priestess-<BR>Cazic-Thule</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">dusklar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am sure there is no stacking issue with Shaman Focus, and Cleric Aegolism spell, as I have had them both on me.. However, Armor of Protection will not stack with Focus.  I  trade the few ac pts Armor of Protection gives for Focus because of the additional hps, str, agil, and dex buff it gives.  <P>Dusklar 60th High Priest</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lorken</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm guessing he meant magician not shaman.  Thats the only class I've ever heard with a stacking issue with an AC buff where they like theirs better.<p>[This message has been edited by Lorken (edited 06-08-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gello</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I asked a shaman, and he said the only stacking issue he could think of was Shroud of Spirits (54 shm AC buff).  Aegis and BoF have more AC, so it's preferrable to the shaman equivalent.<P>So yeah he probably meant mages' Phantom Armor.  Especially for those with mana robe, the regen is nice.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arianae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bah, they are right, the mages get pissed b/c of the phantom armor series stacking issues, but it's not like stacking issues have ever stopped VI before.<P>Personally it's not me casting something on th